": 3828, \"to\": 4064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4048, \"end\": 4063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He finished in 43.40 seconds, beating Britain's Matthew Hudson-Smith by .04 seconds; they are now the fourth- and fifth-fastest men in history at the distance.\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4103, \"end\": 4110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9740658377479549, \"rank\": 0.026624436519391545, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4113, \"end\": 4133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Hudson-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall's late push came the evening afterAmerican Cole Hocker rocked his sport by coming from way backto beat the favorites in a memorable men's 1500.\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4274, \"end\": 4285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cole Hocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add in Noah Lyles, whose only lead in his100-meter thrillerSunday came at the exact point he crossed the finish line, and it's easy to see a pattern.\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4383, \"end\": 4393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got determination,\\\" Hall said.\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what got me to that line.\", \"from\": 4566, \"to\": 4599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of hurt, a lot of pain.\\\"\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The win came about an hour after Lyles advanced to the final of the 200 meters despitefinishing secondto Letsile Tebogo in his semifinal.\", \"from\": 4632, \"to\": 4769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4665, \"end\": 4670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9968095228832464, \"rank\": 0.0031997180287909027, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles will race for the gold medal Thursday.\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Things looked bad for Hall, a 26-year-old who starred at South Carolina and who breeds dogs, as the eight sprinters approached the final curve.\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4875, \"end\": 4889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Carolina_Gamecocks_football\", \"score\": 0.5430238272090235, \"rank\": 0.8161770380397625, \"text\": \"South Carolina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Carolina_Gamecocks_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Carolina_Gamecocks_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was 5 or so meters behind Hudson-Smith and 2012 champion Kirani James, both to his left, and as they rounded the bend, Hall was making up ground on Jareem Richards to his outside.\", \"from\": 4963, \"to\": 5145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5023, \"end\": 5029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirani\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirani\"}, {\"begin\": 5030, \"end\": 5035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.8860550661719634, \"rank\": 0.1164558493110083, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It looked to be shaping up as a good battle for bronze.\", \"from\": 5146, \"to\": 5201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With his arms pumping low and wide and his head bobbing, Hall passed them all, then thrust his chest out to beat the Brit.\", \"from\": 5203, \"to\": 5325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall fell to the ground and scissored his arms and legs back and forth - snow angels in 80-degree weather on the bright purple track.\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just wanted to keep doing what my coach told me to do, just keep driving and keep driving and get home,\\\" Hall said.\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lost in that chaos was Samukonga, the Zambian, who also came from nowhere to take third.\", \"from\": 5581, \"to\": 5669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5619, \"end\": 5626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999852229849, \"rank\": 1.4776886033854429e-08, \"text\": \"Zambian\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall is the first American since LaShawn Merritt in 2008 to capture gold in the one-lap race that the country dominated for decades before that.\", \"from\": 5671, \"to\": 5815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5689, \"end\": 5697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986757303548294, \"rank\": 0.001318728327358287, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5704, \"end\": 5719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LaShawn Merritt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joins the likes of Michael Johnson, Jeremy Wariner and Lee Evans among the champions the United States has produced in the most tactical sprint on the track program.\", \"from\": 5816, \"to\": 5984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5838, \"end\": 5853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"score\": 0.6562406956374156, \"rank\": 0.2753288987434648, \"text\": \"Michael Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\"}, {\"begin\": 5855, \"end\": 5869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Wariner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeremy Wariner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Wariner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Wariner\"}, {\"begin\": 5908, \"end\": 5921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999761376443746, \"rank\": 0.00023253805651320914, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew these guys would get out try to see who they could throw off their race,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 5986, \"to\": 6076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Turns out, not him.\", \"from\": 6078, \"to\": 6097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new champ's reaction when he crossed the line: \\\"I just won.\", \"from\": 6099, \"to\": 6162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's over.\", \"from\": 6163, \"to\": 6173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next four years, I can say I am Olympic champion.\\\"\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Morocco's Soufiane El Bakkali defended his title in men's steeplechase, finishing in 8 minutes, 6.05 seconds for a .36-second win over America's Kenneth Rooks.\", \"from\": 6226, \"to\": 6385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6226, \"end\": 6233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9508242569443899, \"rank\": 0.05171906646772235, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6236, \"end\": 6255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane El Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooks had the lead heading into the homestretch and was looking to pull off a massive upset, but El Bakkali overtook him.\", \"from\": 6387, \"to\": 6508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6487, \"end\": 6494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\", \"score\": 0.9999999977471816, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooks still beat his personal best by almost 9 seconds to capture the second silver over three Olympics in the event for America.\", \"from\": 6510, \"to\": 6639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Evan Jager finished second in 2016.\", \"from\": 6641, \"to\": 6676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6641, \"end\": 6651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Jager\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evan Jager\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Jager\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Jager\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nina Kennedy's title in pole vault gave Australia its 18th gold medal of the Paris Games, an Olympic record for the country.\", \"from\": 6678, \"to\": 6802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6678, \"end\": 6690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999999998408384, \"rank\": 1.590480996232806e-10, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 6718, \"end\": 6727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9986955209682343, \"rank\": 0.0012599627138964828, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kennedy cleared 4.95 meters to beat defending champion Katie Moon of the U.S.  One of France's up-and-coming track stars, Clement Ducos, outraced Tokyo bronze medalist Alison dos Santos to the line to finish second in the semifinals of the men's 400 hurdles.\", \"from\": 6804, \"to\": 7062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6804, \"end\": 6811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999301554721347, \"rank\": 6.9849406605683e-05, \"text\": \"Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 6865, \"end\": 6869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.604094390794123e-15, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}, {\"begin\": 6890, \"end\": 6896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9361841427656533, \"rank\": 0.06757992938882289, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6934, \"end\": 6939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"score\": 0.8544211278726047, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ducos\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\"}, {\"begin\": 6950, \"end\": 6955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999336069, \"rank\": 6.631405803403745e-11, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 6972, \"end\": 6989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}, {\"begin\": 6972, \"end\": 6989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The prize for Ducos: A rematch with world-record holder Karsten Warholm of Norway, who won that heat easily in 47.67.\", \"from\": 7064, \"to\": 7181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7078, \"end\": 7083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"score\": 0.8544211278726047, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ducos\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\"}, {\"begin\": 7120, \"end\": 7135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karsten Warholm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\"}, {\"begin\": 7139, \"end\": 7145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9559574140023029, \"rank\": 0.02366677465036522, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Warholm and American Rai Benjamin are expected to vie for the title in Saturday's final.\", \"from\": 7183, \"to\": 7271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7195, \"end\": 7203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986757303548294, \"rank\": 0.001318728327358287, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7204, \"end\": 7216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rai Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dos Santos, the Brazilian bronze medalist in asuper-fast final three years agoin Tokyo, will also be in the lineup.\", \"from\": 7272, \"to\": 7387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7353, \"end\": 7358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999336069, \"rank\": 6.631405803403745e-11, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Completely crazy what I have done here,\\\" Ducos said.\", \"from\": 7389, \"to\": 7442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7431, \"end\": 7436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"score\": 0.8544211278726047, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ducos\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ducos,_Martinique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not scared of anything.\", \"from\": 7443, \"to\": 7472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are people around me racing really well and posting really good times, but I have to believe I can get a medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 7473, \"to\": 7591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Roje Stona won gold for Jamaica in the men's discus, setting an Olympic record with a personal-best of 70 meters (229 feet, 8 inches) on his fourth attempt.\", \"from\": 7593, \"to\": 7749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7617, \"end\": 7624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999986486946035, \"rank\": 1.3513067927798346e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That gives traditionalsprint powerhouse Jamaicafour medals in field events so far at the Paris Games - compared to just one on the track.\", \"from\": 7750, \"to\": 7887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"___  AP Summer Olympics:https://apnews.com/hub/2024-paris-olympic-games          Copyright 2025 The Associated Press.\", \"from\": 7889, \"to\": 8006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 8007, \"to\": 8027, \"entities\": []}]}"